der":"He was godson of a president","body":"Charles Taft Snowdon was the grandnephew and godson of President William Howard Taft. He and his mother moved into the White House for 18 months during the Taft presidency. When Taft later became Chief Justice, Snowdon often visited and sat with the justices at the deliberating roundtable.","number":1},{"header":"He played professional football AND professional baseball","body":"After Yale, Charles Taft Snowdon played fullback for the Pittsburgh Steelers and first base for the Pittsburgh Pirates. Playing professionally in two major sports is extraordinarily rare. He later broadcast radio for a Pittsburgh affiliate and for West Virginia University's championship basketball teams.","number":2},{"header":"He saw Mussolini hanging upside down","body":"As a U.S. Army second lieutenant in WWII, Charles Taft Snowdon was present when Mussolini was executed and his body displayed in Milan in April 1945. 'That was one of his favorite stories,' his wife Margaret told the Orlando Sentinel in 1992. 'He led a charmed life. He loved to tell stories, and he had a great sense of humor.'","number":3}],"bio":{"display_name":"Charles Taft Snowdon","first_name":"Charles","last_name":"Snowdon","married_names":[],"middle_name":"Taft"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"charles-snowdon-1911"},"HD3103":{"id":"HD3103","is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":11,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1912,"month":11,"day":3},"death":{"year":1995,"month":4,"day":29},"parents":{"father_id":"X02084","mother_id":"HD3101"},"marriages":